Article:
Gold was trading higher in morning deals on Tuesday on account of demand for the precious metal from jewellers, investors and retailers.

MCX Gold futures were trading 0.07 per cent up at Rs 29,143 per 10 gram at around 10.30 am (IST), while MCX Silver futures were down 0.23 per cent at Rs 39,085 per 1 kg.

Angel Commodities in a research note said, "We expect gold prices to trade higher continuing its positive momentum from the previous trading session while weak dollar index and thin trade also contributed to the rally."

Meanwhile, benchmark equity indices wiped off some initial gains and were trading almost flat in morning session as banking, auto, FMCG and energy shares witnessed selling despite strong global cues.



