The BSE Sensex was trading 19 points, or 0.06 per cent, up at 33,831, while NSE Nifty index was up 7.70 points, or 0.07 per cent, at 10,443.25.

As many as 27 stocks in the Nifty index were trading in red with Bharti Infratel gaining 2.51 per cent, followed by ONGC (up 1.95 per cent), Tech Mahindra (up 1.75 per cent) and M&M (up 1.31 per cent).

On the other hand, Eicher Motors, Indiabulls Housing Finance, HPCL, BPCL and IOC were down between 0.98 per cent and 2.60 per cent.
